From 8963553e63d7a47ac2b3533820a0c7f9beb0a881 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 13:31:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] log: surface NULL textures from the two silent
 CreateTextureFromSurface sites
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Surface::loadImage (src/graphics/Surface.cpp:46-53) is the only NXEngine
texture-creation site that NULL-checks the SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface
result and emits a LOG_ERROR. Two other sites swallow NULL silently:

  - Renderer::initVideo (src/graphics/Renderer.cpp:189) — _spot_light.
    No NULL check on IMG_Load(spot.png) either.
  - Font::load (src/graphics/Font.cpp:75) — font atlas page textures.
    No NULL check on IMG_Load(atlas) either, and a NULL was getting
    push_back'd into _atlases, then later read via _atlases.at(idx) at
    every text-glyph render.

Why DOS needs this -- specifically, why "log + propagate failure" is the
shape of this fix:

The DOS Phase 7 build reaches the title screen but renders pure black,
with build/stage/debug.log flooded by 1647 instances of
"Renderer::drawSurface: SDL_RenderTexture failed: Parameter 'texture' is
invalid" per session. Bisect (task #5) determined: textures going through
Surface::loadImage are not the source (its NULL-branch logger never
fires); the workaround env var SDL_INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS=0 reaches the
DOS process intact but cannot suppress the errors because SDL3's
SDL_ObjectValid (vendor/SDL/src/SDL_utils_c.h:79-90) tests for NULL
*before* the validation-disabled short-circuit -- so a literal NULL
texture pointer trips the "invalid" path regardless of the hint state.

Net: the 1647 errors must be coming from a NULL texture, and the only
plausible NULL sources in NXEngine are these two silent sites. Without
this patch we have no way to identify which one fires -- the downstream
drawSurface error doesn't carry the create-site identity.

Fix shape (matching Surface.cpp:52's existing pattern):

  - Renderer::initVideo: log on IMG_Load NULL (spot.png missing); log
    on SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface NULL; set _spot_light = NULL
    explicitly on the early-out so the lighting render path can be
    null-checked separately (out of scope for this patch). Continue
    initVideo (return true) -- spotlight is non-fatal.

  - Font::load: log on IMG_Load NULL or texture creation NULL, and
    do NOT push the NULL into _atlases. Page indices may de-sync with
    glyph.atlasid as a result, but the title-screen font typically uses
    a single page; surfacing the failure clearly is more valuable than
    preserving silent-cascade behaviour. If a real font ships with
    multiple pages and a middle page fails, follow-up work can pick a
    different recovery (sentinel, separate index map) -- the missing
    log line was the blocker.

This is a permanent fix, not a one-shot diagnostic: NULL texture from
either site will always be a real bug worth surfacing, and the LOG_ERROR
matches Surface.cpp:52's idiom so future audits read consistently.
---
 src/graphics/Font.cpp     | 13 ++++++++++++-
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 10 ++++++++++
 2 files changed, 22 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Font.cpp b/src/graphics/Font.cpp
index b605d2f..ebf0a00 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Font.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Font.cpp
@@ -72,8 +72,19 @@ bool Font::load()
     {
       std::string atlaspath = ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPath(atlas.get<std::string>());
       SDL_Surface *surf     = IMG_Load(atlaspath.c_str());
-      _atlases.push_back(SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface(Renderer::getInstance()->renderer(), surf));
+      if (!surf)
+      {
+        LOG_ERROR("Font::load: atlas IMG_Load failed for '{}': {}", atlaspath, SDL_GetError());
+        continue;
+      }
+      SDL_Texture *atlas_tex = SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface(Renderer::getInstance()->renderer(), surf);
       SDL_DestroySurface(surf);
+      if (!atlas_tex)
+      {
+        LOG_ERROR("Font::load: atlas SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface failed for '{}': {}", atlaspath, SDL_GetError());
+        continue;
+      }
+      _atlases.push_back(atlas_tex);
     }
   }
   else
diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 3dd970f..77613ef 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -186,7 +186,17 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
 
   SDL_Surface *image;
   image = IMG_Load(spotpath.c_str());
+  if (!image)
+  {
+    LOG_ERROR("Renderer::initVideo: spotlight IMG_Load failed for '{}': {}", spotpath, SDL_GetError());
+    _spot_light = NULL;
+    return true;
+  }
   _spot_light = SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface(_renderer, image);
+  if (!_spot_light)
+  {
+    LOG_ERROR("Renderer::initVideo: spotlight SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface failed: {}", SDL_GetError());
+  }
   SDL_DestroySurface(image);
 
   return true;
-- 
